{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848672637,"sessionID":"ses_2872bf764fferZ1E6JNoYtwbkF","part":{"id":"prt_d78d44d4b001qdJb7MDsicueMT","messageID":"msg_d78d43caf001nUiKtIrHkplxMj","sessionID":"ses_2872bf764fferZ1E6JNoYtwbkF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-08c645d6b761429e9f45eedb34d9bcbe","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/client-go.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/client-go.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # client-go library\n2: \n3: Generated Kubernetes client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1`**, module path **`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`**. Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n4: \n5: ## Clientset\n6: \n7: ### `Interface` (`clientset/versioned/clientset.go`)\n8: \n9: ```go\n10: type Interface interface {\n11: \tDiscovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n12: \tRuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n13: }\n14: ```\n15: \n16: ### `Clientset` struct\n17: \n18: Embeds `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and holds `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`.\n19: \n20: **Constructors**\n21: \n22: - `NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)`\n23: - `NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)`\n24: - `NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *Clientset`\n25: - `New(c rest.Interface) *Clientset`\n26: \n27: **Group accessor:** `RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## Typed client — `runtime/v1alpha1`\n32: \n33: ### `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` (`clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`)\n34: \n35: ```go\n36: type RuntimeV1alpha1Interface interface {\n37: \tRESTClient() rest.Interface\n38: \tAgentRuntimesGetter\n39: \tCodeInterpretersGetter\n40: }\n41: ```\n42: \n43: `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` implements this interface. REST defaults: `GroupVersion` = `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`.SchemeGroupVersion, `APIPath` = `/apis`, negotiated serializer from `clientset/versioned/scheme`.\n44: \n45: ### `AgentRuntimesGetter` / `AgentRuntimeInterface` (`.../agentruntime.go`)\n46: \n47: ```go\n48: type AgentRuntimesGetter interface {\n49: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface\n50: }\n51: \n52: type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n53: \tCreate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n54: \tUpdate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n55: \tUpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n56: \tDelete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n57: \tDeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n58: \tGet(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n59: \tList(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n60: \tWatch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n61: \tPatch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n62: \tAgentRuntimeExpansion\n63: }\n64: ```\n65: \n66: REST resource plural: **`agentruntimes`**.\n67: \n68: ### `CodeInterpretersGetter` / `CodeInterpreterInterface` (`.../codeinterpreter.go`)\n69: \n70: Same method shape as `AgentRuntimeInterface`, types `*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`. REST resource plural: **`codeinterpreters`**.\n71: \n72: ### Expansion hooks (`generated_expansion.go`)\n73: \n74: ```go\n75: type AgentRuntimeExpansion interface{}\n76: type CodeInterpreterExpansion interface{}\n77: ```\n78: \n79: (Empty — reserved for custom methods.)\n80: \n81: ### Fake clients (`typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/`)\n82: \n83: `fake_runtime_client.go`, `fake_agentruntime.go`, `fake_codeinterpreter.go` — test doubles implementing the typed interfaces; `doc.go` markers.\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## Scheme (`clientset/versioned/scheme/`)\n88: \n89: | File | Role |\n90: |------|------|\n91: | `register.go` | Builds `Scheme`, `Codecs`, `ParameterCodec`; `AddToScheme` registers `runtime/v1alpha1` types |\n92: | `doc.go` | Package doc |\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## Informer factory\n97: \n98: ### `SharedInformerFactory` (`informers/externalversions/factory.go`)\n99: \n100: ```go\n101: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n102: \tinternalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory\n103: \tStart(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n104: \tShutdown()\n105: \tWaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool\n106: \tForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error)\n107: \tInformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n108: \tRuntime() externalversionsruntime.Interface\n109: }\n110: ```\n111: \n112: **Constructors / options**\n113: \n114: - `NewSharedInformerFactory(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration)`\n115: - `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, defaultResync, options ...SharedInformerOption)`\n116: - `NewFilteredSharedInformerFactory` (deprecated alias to WithOptions)\n117: - Options: `WithCustomResyncConfig`, `WithTweakListOptions`, `WithNamespace`, `WithTransform`\n118: \n119: ### Group interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go`)\n120: \n121: ```go\n122: type Interface interface {\n123: \tV1alpha1() v1alpha1.Interface\n124: }\n125: ```\n126: \n127: `New(factory, namespace, tweakListOptions)` returns group accessor.\n128: \n129: ### Version interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go`)\n130: \n131: ```go\n132: type Interface interface {\n133: \tAgentRuntimes() AgentRuntimeInformer\n134: \tCodeInterpreters() CodeInterpreterInformer\n135: }\n136: ```\n137: \n138: ### Per-type informers (`.../runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`, `codeinterpreter.go`)\n139: \n140: Example (`AgentRuntimeInformer`):\n141: \n142: ```go\n143: type AgentRuntimeInformer interface {\n144: \tInformer() cache.SharedIndexInformer\n145: \tLister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n146: }\n147: ```\n148: \n149: Also provides `NewAgentRuntimeInformer`, `NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer`, and analogous constructors for CodeInterpreter.\n150: \n151: ### Generic resource routing (`informers/externalversions/generic.go`)\n152: \n153: `ForResource` switches on:\n154: \n155: - `v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\")` → `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()`\n156: - `...WithResource(\"codeinterpreters\")` → `...CodeInterpreters().Informer()`\n157: \n158: ### `internalinterfaces` (`informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go`)\n159: \n160: ```go\n161: type NewInformerFunc func(versioned.Interface, time.Duration) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n162: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n163: \tStart(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n164: \tInformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n165: }\n166: type TweakListOptionsFunc func(*metav1.ListOptions)\n167: ```\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## Listers (`listers/runtime/v1alpha1/`)\n172: \n173: ### `AgentRuntimeLister` / `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` (`agentruntime.go`)\n174: \n175: ```go\n176: type AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n177: \tList(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n178: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n179: \tAgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n180: }\n181: \n182: type AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n183: \tList(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n184: \tGet(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n185: \tAgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n186: }\n187: ```\n188: \n189: `NewAgentRuntimeLister` uses `runtimev1alpha1.Resource(\"agentruntime\").GroupResource()`.\n190: \n191: ### `CodeInterpreterLister` / `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` (`codeinterpreter.go`)\n192: \n193: Same pattern for `CodeInterpreter`; `NewCodeInterpreterLister` uses `Resource(\"codeinterpreter\").GroupResource()`.\n194: \n195: ### Expansion (`expansion_generated.go`)\n196: \n197: Empty expansion interfaces for listers and namespace listers (all four types).\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## Fake clientset (`clientset/versioned/fake/`)\n202: \n203: | File | Role |\n204: |------|------|\n205: | `clientset_generated.go` | `NewSimpleClientset`, `NewClientset` — in-memory fake `Clientset` |\n206: | `register.go` | Scheme registration for fakes |\n207: | `doc.go` | Package doc |\n208: \n209: ---\n210: \n211: ## File index (all paths under `client-go/`)\n212: \n213: | Path | Role |\n214: |------|------|\n215: | `clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | `Clientset`, `Interface`, constructors |\n216: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | Scheme / codecs for generated client |\n217: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go` | Doc |\n218: | `clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go` | Fake clientset implementation |\n219: | `clientset/versioned/fake/register.go` | Fake scheme wiring |\n220: | `clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n221: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` |\n222: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, typed REST client |\n223: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterInterface`, typed REST client |\n224: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` | Expansion interfaces |\n225: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Doc |\n226: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go` | Fake runtime group client |\n227: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go` | Fake AgentRuntime client |\n228: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` | Fake CodeInterpreter client |\n229: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n230: | `informers/externalversions/factory.go` | `SharedInformerFactory`, options, `Start`/`Shutdown`/`WaitForCacheSync` |\n231: | `informers/externalversions/generic.go` | `GenericInformer`, `ForResource` |\n232: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go` | Group `runtime` informer accessor |\n233: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go` | `v1alpha1` informer accessors |\n234: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | AgentRuntime informer + constructor |\n235: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | CodeInterpreter informer + constructor |\n236: | `informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go` | Small factory interface + `NewInformerFunc`, `TweakListOptionsFunc` |\n237: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeLister`, namespace lister |\n238: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterLister`, namespace lister |\n239: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go` | Lister expansion interfaces |\n240: \n241: **Regeneration:** `make gen-client` → `hack/update-codegen.sh` (`k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1, `--with-watch`, output package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`).\n\n(End of file - total 241 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# client-go library\n\nGenerated Kubernetes client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1`**, module path **`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`**. Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n\n## Clientset\n\n### `Interface` (`clientset/versioned/clientset.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Interface interface {\n\tDiscovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n\tRuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n}\n```\n\n### `Clientset` struct\n\nEmbeds `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and holds `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`.\n\n**Constructors**","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/client-go.md","time":{"start":1775848672621,"end":1775848672635}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848672657,"sessionID":"ses_2872bf764fferZ1E6JNoYtwbkF","part":{"id":"prt_d78d44b25001udfxOKY5ZYNIEb","messageID":"msg_d78d43caf001nUiKtIrHkplxMj","sessionID":"ses_2872bf764fferZ1E6JNoYtwbkF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f80f836bd8e04f94b144400fd71c2942","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Deploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Helm chart installation\n9: The system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n13: - **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n14: - **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\n17: The system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n20: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values\n21: - **WHEN** pods for `workloadmanager` and `agentcube-router` start\n22: - **THEN** each container SHALL have environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` populated from those values\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Workload Manager deployment shape\n25: The system SHALL deploy Workload Manager as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `workloadmanager` with replica count, container image, service type/port, resource requests/limits, health probes, and optional `extraEnv` driven from `values.yaml`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Default replica and service exposure\n28: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n29: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n30: - **THEN** the Workload Manager `Deployment` SHALL use `workloadmanager.replicas` (default 1), expose HTTP on `workloadmanager.service.port` (default 8080), and use liveness/readiness HTTP GET `/health` on that port\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Router deployment shape\n33: The system SHALL deploy the Router as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `agentcube-router` with replica count, image, `ClusterIP` service mapping `port`→`targetPort`, resource requests/limits, optional dedicated `serviceAccountName`, and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` pointing at the in-cluster Workload Manager service.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router reaches Workload Manager by DNS\n36: - **GIVEN** release namespace `N` and Workload Manager service port `P` from values\n37: - **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL have `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` set to `http://workloadmanager.N.svc.cluster.local:P` and container args including `--port=<targetPort>` and `--debug`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Workload Manager ClusterRole permissions\n41: The system SHALL create a `ServiceAccount` `workloadmanager`, a `ClusterRole` `workloadmanager`, and `ClusterRoleBinding` `workloadmanager` granting the rules required for agent-sandbox, AgentCube runtime CRDs, core workloads, auth, and secrets.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Binding ties SA to cluster role\n44: - **GIVEN** chart installation in namespace `N`\n45: - **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n46: - **THEN** subject `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in namespace `N` SHALL be bound to `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` via `ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Optional Router namespace Role\n49: The system SHALL optionally create namespace-scoped `ServiceAccount`, `Role`, and `RoleBinding` for the Router when `router.rbac.create` is true, granting secret management in that namespace.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: RBAC off by default\n52: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: false`\n53: - **WHEN** the chart renders templates\n54: - **THEN** Router optional RBAC manifests SHALL NOT be emitted\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: RBAC on with named service account\n57: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` and `router.serviceAccountName` set (or defaulted by template to `agentcube-router`)\n58: - **WHEN** the chart is applied\n59: - **THEN** Router pods MAY use that `serviceAccountName` and the Role SHALL allow verbs on `secrets` in the release namespace\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Optional Volcano agent scheduler\n62: The system SHALL optionally deploy Volcano agent scheduler resources (ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment) when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Scheduler disabled\n65: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (default)\n66: - **WHEN** templates render\n67: - **THEN** no Volcano scheduler objects SHALL be created\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: CRDs shipped with the chart\n70: The system SHALL ship `CustomResourceDefinition` manifests for `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters` under the chart `crds/` directory so Helm installs them with the chart lifecycle.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: CRD group and scope\n73: - **GIVEN** chart path `manifests/charts/base`\n74: - **WHEN** CRD YAML is applied\n75: - **THEN** both CRDs SHALL use API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, and `scope: Namespaced`\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Docker images for core binaries\n78: The system SHALL provide Dockerfiles to build three images: Workload Manager (`docker/Dockerfile`), Router (`docker/Dockerfile.router`), and picod (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`).\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Multi-stage Go build for control plane\n81: - **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n82: - **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile` (or `Dockerfile.router`) runs\n83: - **THEN** the image SHALL compile the respective Go binary with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and run it from Alpine 3.19 as a non-root user (`apiserver` UID 1000 or `router` UID 1000) exposing port 8080\n84: \n85: ### Requirement: Makefile build targets\n86: The system SHALL expose Make targets to build binaries (`build`, related targets), run tests (`test`), build/push Docker images (`docker-*`), run code generation (`generate`, `gen-crd`, `gen-client`, `gen-all`, `gen-check`), and run E2E (`e2e`, `e2e-clean`).\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Default `make` builds workload manager\n89: - **GIVEN** Go toolchain and generated code prerequisites\n90: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make` (default `all` → `build`)\n91: - **THEN** `bin/workloadmanager` SHALL be produced from `./cmd/workload-manager` after `generate`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: E2E entrypoint\n94: - **GIVEN** Kind, kubectl, Docker, Helm, and curl available\n95: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make e2e`\n96: - **THEN** the repository SHALL execute `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` which provisions the cluster (unless skipped), deploys dependencies, and runs Go and Python E2E tests\n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Specification\n\n## Purpose\nDeploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Helm chart installation\nThe system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n\n#### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n- **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n- **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n\n### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\nThe system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n\n#### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n- **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/spec.md","time":{"start":1775848672616,"end":1775848672638}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775848672687,"sessionID":"ses_2872bf764fferZ1E6JNoYtwbkF","part":{"id":"prt_d78d44d80001HMInQleMVuKkj5","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d78d43caf001nUiKtIrHkplxMj","sessionID":"ses_2872bf764fferZ1E6JNoYtwbkF","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":23243,"input":2379,"output":193,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":20671}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775848676695,"sessionID":"ses_2872bf764fferZ1E6JNoYtwbkF","part":{"id":"prt_d78d45d56001bzZgcJrVlLWPrF","messageID":"msg_d78d44dd0001QdRm1McRnyEGlG","sessionID":"ses_2872bf764fferZ1E6JNoYtwbkF","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775848719416,"sessionID":"ses_2872bf764fferZ1E6JNoYtwbkF","part":{"id":"prt_d78d471e3001S6e4xn7iOJ5vpD","messageID":"msg_d78d44dd0001QdRm1McRnyEGlG","sessionID":"ses_2872bf764fferZ1E6JNoYtwbkF","type":"text","text":"Now I'll write the delta-spec.md for AR-009 focusing on the Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core functionality.","time":{"start":1775848719414,"end":1775848719414}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848719495,"sessionID":"ses_2872bf764fferZ1E6JNoYtwbkF","part":{"id":"prt_d78d50439001arA1rgieFwMBpZ","messageID":"msg_d78d44dd0001QdRm1McRnyEGlG","sessionID":"ses_2872bf764fferZ1E6JNoYtwbkF","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-adaa27887e064787b29d9c1c73b76344","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-009 Delta-Spec\n\n## Purpose\nImplement the core HTTP reverse proxy functionality for the Router component, providing request routing to sandbox endpoints with JWT authentication, health endpoints, and concurrency management.\n\n## Base Specs\n- deployment/client-go.md: Kubernetes client library for runtime API types (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: HTTP server initialization\nThe system SHALL provide a configurable HTTP server that listens on a specified port, supports both HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2 (h2c), with configurable timeouts and optional TLS support.\n\n#### Scenario: Server starts on configured port\n- **GIVEN** `NewServer` is called with `Port: 8080`\n- **WHEN** `Start` is invoked\n- **THEN** the server listens on port 8080 and accepts HTTP connections\n\n#### Scenario: Server starts with TLS enabled\n- **GIVEN** `NewServer` is called with `EnableTLS: true`, `TLSCertPath: \"/certs/cert.pem\"`, and `TLSKeyPath: \"/certs/key.pem\"`\n- **WHEN** `Start` is invoked\n- **THEN** the server uses TLS with the provided certificate and key files\n\n#### Scenario: Server fails with invalid TLS configuration\n- **GIVEN** `NewServer` is called with `EnableTLS: true` and empty cert or key path\n- **WHEN** `Start` is invoked\n- **THEN** it returns an error indicating certificate and key are required\n\n#### Scenario: Server applies configured timeouts\n- **GIVEN** `NewServer` is called with `ReadTimeout: 30s` and `IdleTimeout: 90s`\n- **WHEN** the server is running\n- **THEN** HTTP reads timeout after 30s and idle connections close after 90s\n\n#### Scenario: Server shuts down gracefully\n- **GIVEN** the server is running and context is cancelled\n- **WHEN** shutdown is triggered\n- **THEN** the server stops accepting new connections and waits up to 10s for active connections to complete\n\n### Requirement: Reverse proxy configuration\nThe system SHALL provide reverse proxy functionality to forward HTTP requests to upstream sandbox endpoints, handling URL construction, protocol detection, and proper request/response forwarding.\n\n#### Scenario: Proxy forwards to upstream endpoint\n- **GIVEN** a reverse proxy is configured with upstream URL `http://sandbox-pod:8080`\n- **WHEN** an incoming request is received\n- **THEN** the proxy forwards the request to the upstream URL and returns the response\n\n#### Scenario: Proxy constructs URL with protocol prefix\n- **GIVEN** sandbox info with `Protocol: \"http\"` and `Endpoint: \"sandbox-pod:8080\"`\n- **WHEN** the upstream URL is constructed\n- **THEN** the URL becomes `http://sandbox-pod:8080`\n\n#### Scenario: Proxy uses endpoint as-is when scheme present\n- **GIVEN** sandbox info with `Protocol: \"\"` and `Endpoint: \"https://sandbox-pod:8080\"`\n- **WHEN** the upstream URL is constructed\n- **THEN** the URL remains `https://sandbox-pod:8080`\n\n#### Scenario: Proxy handles multiple entry points\n- **GIVEN** sandbox info with entry points `[{\"path\": \"/api\", \"endpoint\": \"api:8080\"}, {\"path\": \"/\", \"endpoint\": \"web:8080\"}]`\n- **WHEN** a request to `/api/v1/data` is received\n- **THEN** the proxy routes to `api:8080`\n\n#### Scenario: Proxy uses first entry point for non-matching paths\n- **GIVEN** sandbox info with entry points `[{\"path\": \"/api\", \"endpoint\": \"api:8080\"}, {\"path\": \"/\", \"endpoint\": \"web:8080\"}]`\n- **WHEN** a request to `/health` is received\n- **THEN** the proxy routes to `web:8080` (first entry point with path \"/\")\n\n### Requirement: Request forwarding headers\nThe system SHALL set standard forwarding headers on proxied requests, including X-Forwarded-Host, X-Forwarded-Proto, and X-Forwarded-For.\n\n#### Scenario: Proxy sets X-Forwarded-Host\n- **GIVEN** an incoming request with Host header `example.com`\n- **WHEN** the proxy forwards the request\n- **THEN** the proxied request includes `X-Forwarded-Host: example.com`\n\n#### Scenario: Proxy sets X-Forwarded-Proto based on TLS\n- **GIVEN** TLS is enabled and an incoming request is received\n- **WHEN** the proxy forwards the request\n- **THEN** the proxied request includes `X-Forwarded-Proto: https`\n\n#### Scenario: Proxy sets X-Forwarded-Proto to http without TLS\n- **GIVEN** TLS is disabled and an incoming request is received\n- **WHEN** the proxy forwards the request\n- **THEN** the proxied request includes `X-Forwarded-Proto: http`\n\n#### Scenario: Proxy appends client IP to X-Forwarded-For\n- **GIVEN** an incoming request from client IP `10.0.0.5` and existing `X-Forwarded-For: 10.0.0.1`\n- **WHEN** the proxy forwards the request\n- **THEN** the proxied request includes `X-Forwarded-For: 10.0.0.1, 10.0.0.5`\n\n### Requirement: JWT signing and injection\nThe system SHALL generate and sign JWT tokens for authenticated requests to sandbox endpoints, injecting the token into the Authorization header.\n\n#### Scenario: Proxy generates JWT for sandbox request\n- **GIVEN** a JWT manager is configured with a signing key and the request target requires JWT\n- **WHEN** the proxy forwards a request\n- **THEN** the proxied request includes `Authorization: Bearer <signed-jwt>`\n\n#### Scenario: JWT signing failure blocks proxy\n- **GIVEN** JWT generation returns an error during request forwarding\n- **WHEN** the proxy attempts to forward the request\n- **THEN** the handler returns 500 with JSON `{\"code\":\"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\",\"error\":\"failed to sign request\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: JWT manager loads keys from secret\n- **GIVEN** the JWT manager is initialized with secret `picod-router-identity` containing `private.pem` and `public.pem`\n- **WHEN** the server starts\n- **THEN** the JWT manager successfully loads the signing key from `private.pem`\n\n### Requirement: Proxy error handling\nThe system SHALL map reverse proxy errors to appropriate HTTP status codes and error messages for upstream failures.\n\n#### Scenario: Connection refused maps to 502\n- **GIVEN** the upstream endpoint refuses the connection\n- **WHEN** the proxy error handler is invoked\n- **THEN** the response is 502 with JSON `{\"error\":\"sandbox unreachable\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout maps to 504\n- **GIVEN** the upstream endpoint times out\n- **WHEN** the proxy error handler is invoked\n- **THEN** the response is 504 with JSON `{\"error\":\"sandbox timeout\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Other errors map to 502\n- **GIVEN** the upstream endpoint returns any other error\n- **WHEN** the proxy error handler is invoked\n- **THEN** the response is 502 with JSON `{\"error\":\"sandbox unreachable\"}`\n\n### Requirement: Health endpoints\nThe system SHALL provide liveness and readiness endpoints for health checking.\n\n#### Scenario: Liveness endpoint returns success\n- **GIVEN** the server is running\n- **WHEN** `GET /health/live` is called\n- **THEN** the response is 200 with JSON `{\"status\":\"alive\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Readiness endpoint returns success when dependencies ready\n- **GIVEN** all required dependencies (session manager, JWT manager) are initialized\n- **WHEN** `GET /health/ready` is called\n- **THEN** the response is 200 with JSON `{\"status\":\"ready\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Readiness endpoint returns 503 when dependencies missing\n- **GIVEN** the session manager is not initialized\n- **WHEN** `GET /health/ready` is called\n- **THEN** the response is 503 with JSON including `\"error\":\"session manager not available\"`\n\n### Requirement: Concurrency limiting\nThe system SHALL apply a semaphore middleware to limit concurrent requests, preventing server overload.\n\n#### Scenario: Requests within limit are processed\n- **GIVEN** concurrency limit is 1000 and 500 concurrent requests are active\n- **WHEN** a new request arrives\n- **THEN** the request is processed normally\n\n#### Scenario: Requests over limit are rejected\n- **GIVEN** concurrency limit is 1000 and 1000 concurrent requests are active\n- **WHEN** a new request arrives\n- **THEN** the response is 429 with JSON `{\"error\":\"server overloaded, please try again later\",\"code\":\"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Default limit when config is zero\n- **GIVEN** `MaxConcurrentRequests` is set to 0\n- **WHEN** the server is initialized\n- **THEN** the effective limit is set to 1000\n\n### Requirement: Route registration\nThe system SHALL register HTTP routes for invocation endpoints, applying appropriate middleware chains.\n\n#### Scenario: Agent runtime invocation route is registered\n- **GIVEN** the server is initialized\n- **WHEN** routes are registered\n- **THEN** GET and POST are registered for `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path`\n\n#### Scenario: Code interpreter invocation route is registered\n- **GIVEN** the server is initialized\n- **WHEN** routes are registered\n- **THEN** GET and POST are registered for `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path`\n\n#### Scenario: Middleware chain is applied to v1 routes\n- **GIVEN** the server is initialized with logger, recovery, and concurrency middleware\n- **WHEN** routes under `/v1` are registered\n- **THEN** all v1 routes use the configured middleware chain\n\n### Requirement: Response headers\nThe system SHALL add response headers to indicate the session ID used for processing the request.\n\n#### Scenario: Session ID header is added to response\n- **GIVEN** a request is processed with session ID `abc123`\n- **WHEN** the response is sent\n- **THEN** the response includes header `x-agentcube-session-id: abc123`\n\n### Requirement: Path normalization\nThe system SHALL normalize request paths when forwarding, ensuring proper slash handling.\n\n#### Scenario: Path prefix is added when missing\n- **GIVEN** a Gin path parameter `api/v1/data` (without leading slash)\n- **WHEN** the director constructs the outbound path\n- **THEN** the path becomes `/api/v1/data`\n\n### Requirement: Shared HTTP transport\nThe system SHALL use a shared HTTP transport across all reverse proxy instances for optimal resource usage.\n\n#### Scenario: Multiple proxies share transport\n- **GIVEN** the server creates multiple reverse proxy instances\n- **WHEN** proxies are initialized\n- **THEN** all proxies share the same `http.Transport` instance\n\n### Requirement: Configuration validation\nThe system SHALL validate required configuration at server initialization.\n\n#### Scenario: Missing required port fails initialization\n- **GIVEN** `NewServer` is called without specifying port\n- **WHEN** initialization is attempted\n- **THEN** it returns an error indicating port is required\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid port number fails initialization\n- **GIVEN** `NewServer` is called with `Port: -1`\n- **WHEN** initialization is attempted\n- **THEN** it returns an error indicating invalid port number","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775848719474,"end":1775848719492}}}}
